#### **ROBOTS IN ACTION**

## **How robots are transforming the world around us**

View image: (https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/42731543-fc86-4899-bba2-e92ef227fbbe/Group_1000005225__1_.jpg?t=1778290844)
Follow image link: (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2el-7A2sgN4)
Caption: Click here to watch robot monk Gabi take part in a Buddhist initiation ceremony this week. Photo: Lee Jin-man/AP 

🙏 **Motor Monk: **A humanoid robot named Gabi became the first non-human to [participate](https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/meet-gabi-the-new-robot-monk-at-a-buddhist-temple-in-south-korea-its-the-latest-robot-to-take-up-religious-practice-180988695/) in a Buddhist initiation ceremony in South Korea, joining monks in prayer, bowing, and formally pledging devotion. Temple organizers adapted the traditional Five Precepts for the robot with help from ChatGPT and Gemini — a symbolic step that Buddhist leaders say reflects serious thinking about humans and machines sharing spaces. Watch the robotic monk in action [here](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2el-7A2sgN4). 

🎶 **Sing It Out:** Humanoid robot Sophia [took the stage](https://www.reuters.com/video/watch/idRW671729042026RP1/) with the Baptist University Symphony Orchestra in Hong Kong, performing at an AI-themed gala concert designed to merge classical music with emerging technology. The concert marked Sophia's first foray into live classical performance and signals a growing cultural ambition for humanoid robots to move into spaces previously reserved entirely for human expression. You can see the robot hit the high notes [here](https://www.reuters.com/video/watch/idRW671729042026RP1/). 

📈 **Playing to Win:** A decade ago, China spotted the EV wave early, subsidized its way to dominance, and undercut every competitor on price. Now, Morgan Stanley claims the country is running the same [playbook](https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-05-07/humanoid-robots-to-power-next-leg-of-china-s-export-dominance) with humanoid robots. Chinese manufacturers already account for around 90% of global humanoid shipments, with costs running at least 20% below foreign equivalents. Analysts now project China's export share will rise from 15% to 16.5% by 2030. 

———————————————————————————

#### **INDUSTRY SNAPSHOT**

## **Everything else you need to know this week**

View image: (https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/76b0d6cf-a489-403a-8995-5ad7341f21cf/image_-_2026-05-09T025707.162.jpg?t=1778291837)
Caption: Photo: 1X Technologies

Here are the biggest developments in the robotics space that you should know about:

* **OpenAI** [reportedly](https://www.wsj.com/tech/ahead-of-race-to-ipo-openai-discussed-spinning-out-robotics-hardware-divisions-18c89706) explored spinning off its robotics unit into a standalone company as it weighs an Alphabet Inc-style structure ahead of a potential IPO.

* **California **will begin [issuing](https://www.cnet.com/tech/services-and-software/californias-driverless-cars-will-be-subject-to-tickets-soon) traffic tickets directly to companies like Waymo and Tesla when their driverless cars break the rules, starting in July. 

* **AGIBOT **turned heads at the 2026 Met Gala, where its A2 humanoid robot made a [surprise appearance](https://interestingengineering.com/ai-robotics/agibot-a2-makes-history-at-met-gala) in a collaboration with designer Alexander Wang.

* **Linkerbot**, which claims to control roughly 80% of the market for dexterous humanoid robot hands, is [eying](https://www.reuters.com/world/china-robot-hand-building-unicorn-linkerbot-targets-6-billion-valuation-2026-05-04/) a $6B valuation in its next funding round.

* **1X **has [opened](https://www.forbes.com/sites/johnkoetsier/2026/04/30/1x-kicks-off-full-scale-production-of-humanoid-robot-neo/) its 58,000-square-foot NEO factory in Hayward, launching what it says is the most vertically integrated humanoid robot production facility in the U.S.

